Aloha all,

This is an informational post that other Mac users of RdbiPgSQL might wish 
to augment for the benefit of future users.

After a recent successful source installation of RdbiPgSQL from 
BioConductor, I tried to install it on a second Mac.  This installation 
failed to find bundle1.so.  I found this file in \usr\lib\ on the first 
Mac and copied it over to the second Mac.  Once this was done RdbiPgSQL 
installed properly.

I had thought the two Macs were set up the same, though the setups took 
place about a year apart.  If someone knows where /usr/lib/bundle1.so 
comes from, this information might help other Mac users down the road.

Thanks again for your earlier help.

Tom

